DVSsitchLiveCD - start with a Ubuntu Live CD (desktop install CD) 
and adds the dvswitch suite and other apps related to recording technical talks.
http://dvswitch.alioth.debian.org/wiki/livecd
http://mirror.anl.gov/pub/ubuntu-iso/CDs/jaunty/ubuntu-9.04-desktop-i386.iso


uniso.sh - # expands a ubuntu live CD so you can hack on it. mounts the iso, copies out the files, including extracing the files from the squashfs file.

chroot.sh - chroots into the extracted CD files, runs inroot.sh, cleans up.
inroot.sh - removes some stuff, adds some stuff, tweaks some stuff.
inroottest.sh - used to figure out why inroot.sh is messing things up.

mkiso.sh - makes an iso image out of all the files.

qemu.sh - boots the CD image
